The paper introduces a new measure, the prediction value, for players' informational importance in probabilistic TU games. This topic falls under game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves decision-making and strategic behavior. The paper also discusses the properties of the prediction value, which involves mathematical analysis and modeling, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper touches on power indices, which are commonly used in social choice theory (cs.SI).
